        [
            "<b>[A] Eight days, etc.:</b> It is written in the Shiltei Giborim that is around the Gemara: It is because they dedicated the Temple then, after the service had been abolished by the Greeks. And the Baal HaItim wrote it is because they abolished circumcision which is on the eighth day. To here [are his words]. But the Knesset Gedolah challenged [this]: Behold the reason is in the Talmud, that it is because of the miracle of the [oil]! So we must say that they wanted to answer the question - is it not that the miracle of the [oil] was only for seven days (since there was enough oil for one day)!?! However I don't know how the first explanation answers this challenge. To here [are his words]. Yet, in my humble opinion, there is not challenge at all. For in the Book of the Maccabees, in the hymn for the second Shabbat of Chanukkah and in Megillat Taanit, it is clearly found that they dedicated it for those eight days, since the Greeks had dirtied and demolished the altar. So they built it anew and dedicated it."
